==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Resorption
<hw>Re*sorp"tion</hw> <pr>(r?*s?rp"sh?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of resorbing; also, the act of absorbing again;
reabsorption.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Petrography)</fld> <def>The redissolving wholly or
in part, in the molten magma of an igneous rock, of crystals previously
formed. The dissolved material may again solidify, giving rise to a mass
of small crystals, usually of a different kind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Resort</ent>⟦br⟧
